the most popular


2159
01:39:29.146 --> 01:39:31.649
and commercially successful
act in the world,


2160
01:39:31.691 --> 01:39:34.443
Lennon was now breaking
every rule imaginable.


2161
01:39:34.485 --> 01:39:37.739
Yet the anger in some
quarters of the counterculture


2162
01:39:37.780 --> 01:39:40.115
toward the song
Revolution also led him


2163
01:39:40.157 --> 01:39:41.659
into a greater political role.

2164
01:39:41.701 --> 01:39:45.663
In 1969, as Richard
Nixon was sworn in


2165
01:39:45.705 --> 01:39:47.456
as the new President of America,

2166
01:39:47.498 --> 01:39:49.417
John Lennon and Yoko Ono emerged

2167
01:39:49.458 --> 01:39:53.046
as the world's most
prominent activists.


2168
01:39:53.086 --> 01:39:55.130
When Lennon came out and said,

2169
01:39:55.172 --> 01:39:57.383
if you're talking about
destruction, count me out,


2170
01:39:57.425 --> 01:40:01.303
he was terribly criticized
by the hard Left.


2171
01:40:01.345 --> 01:40:04.265
And it seems to me that
his reaction to that


2172
01:40:04.306 --> 01:40:07.351
was not to change his
mind about destruction,


2173
01:40:07.393 --> 01:40:09.311
but actually to say,

2174
01:40:09.353 --> 01:40:12.440
"No, I really don't think
the answer is destruction.


2175
01:40:12.481 --> 01:40:15.234
I think the answer
actually is peace."


2176
01:40:15.276 --> 01:40:17.445
[Narrator] In March 1969,

2177
01:40:17.486 --> 01:40:20.073
John Lennon and Yoko
Ono were married.


2178
01:40:20.113 --> 01:40:22.241
With their honeymoon,
the couple embarked


2179
01:40:22.283 --> 01:40:24.953
on a high-profile
campaign for peace,


2180
01:40:24.994 --> 01:40:28.873
presented as a series of
conceptual art events.


2181
01:40:28.915 --> 01:40:32.043
In the spirit of The Beatles'
initial attitude to the press,


2182
01:40:32.085 --> 01:40:35.588
the first of these took place
in their hotel bridal suite,


2183
01:40:35.630 --> 01:40:37.381
in which they
invited journalists


2184
01:40:37.423 --> 01:40:40.342
to discuss politics
openly and frankly.


2185
01:40:40.384 --> 01:40:42.344
[ Yoko Ono ]
This is for world peace.


2186
01:40:42.386 --> 01:40:47.809
And we're thinking that
instead of going out and fight,


2187
01:40:47.850 --> 01:40:50.269
and make war,
something like that,


2188
01:40:50.311 --> 01:40:52.271
we should just stay in bed,

2189
01:40:52.313 --> 01:40:55.817
everybody should just stay
in bed and enjoy the spring.


2190
01:40:55.858 --> 01:40:59.152
He put his career right on
the line there for his beliefs.


2191
01:40:59.194 --> 01:41:01.823
And you have to applaud
him for that, of course.


2192
01:41:01.864 --> 01:41:05.868
It brought him an awful lot
of harassment and trouble.


2193
01:41:05.910 --> 01:41:07.745
[Interviewer]
While you're in bed


2194
01:41:07.787 --> 01:41:10.957
and you're giving your press
conferences in pillow cases,


2195
01:41:10.999 --> 01:41:13.250
are you laughing at us?
- No, no.


2196
01:41:13.292 --> 01:41:15.044
No more than you're
laughing at us.


2197
01:41:15.086 --> 01:41:17.296
We have a laugh, we
think it's funny,


2198
01:41:17.338 --> 01:41:20.842
the fact that the front
page news should be the fact


2199
01:41:20.883 --> 01:41:23.302
that two people went to
bed on their honeymoon.


2200
01:41:23.344 --> 01:41:25.054
We see the funny side of it.

2201
01:41:25.096 --> 01:41:27.890
And that in Vienna, which
is a pretty square place,


2202
01:41:27.932 --> 01:41:30.018
there's all these
beautiful photographs


2203
01:41:30.059 --> 01:41:33.521
of microphones
being held to a bag,


2204
01:41:33.562 --> 01:41:35.188
to wait for the bag to speak.

2205
01:41:35.230 --> 01:41:36.649
It's rather nice.

2206
01:41:36.691 --> 01:41:39.401
But we're serious
about the peace bit.


2207
01:41:39.443 --> 01:41:42.738
Brave, foolhardy,
they were all of that.


2208
01:41:42.780 --> 01:41:44.740
But who else would
have done that then?


2209
01:41:44.782 --> 01:41:47.451
It would be front page
news if they were in bed,


2210
01:41:47.493 --> 01:41:49.704
talking about peace.

2211
01:41:49.745 --> 01:41:52.832
John didn't know
necessarily the ins and outs


2212
01:41:52.874 --> 01:41:54.333
of the whole Vietnam thing.

2213
01:41:54.375 --> 01:41:56.669
He and Yoko knew
that it was wrong


2214
01:41:56.711 --> 01:41:59.547
to be dropping
napalm on villages


2215
01:41:59.588 --> 01:42:01.883
and stripping the
skin off children.


2216
01:42:01.924 --> 01:42:05.594
I mean, he wasn't
wrong in that thinking.


2217
01:42:05.636 --> 01:42:08.181
He really wasn't wrong.

2218
01:42:08.221 --> 01:42:10.307
[Narrator] As the
couple's honeymoon moved


2219
01:42:10.349 --> 01:42:12.018
from Europe to Canada,

2220
01:42:12.060 --> 01:42:14.269
they were joined in their
hotel room by Timothy Leary,


2221
01:42:14.311 --> 01:42:17.356
Allen Ginsberg and a variety
of counterculture figures,


2222
01:42:17.398 --> 01:42:20.442
to record an anthem
for their campaign.


2223
01:42:20.484 --> 01:42:22.486
And where their
experimental records


2224
01:42:22.528 --> 01:42:25.823
and their public appearances
had left many confused,


2225
01:42:25.865 --> 01:42:27.867
this song managed to
bring their message


2226
01:42:27.909 --> 01:42:29.326
to a global audience.

2227
01:42:29.368 --> 01:42:32.371
Give Peace a Chance
was his attempt


2228
01:42:32.413 --> 01:42:36.584
to do something in his own
terms that was actually useful


2229
01:42:36.625 --> 01:42:39.128
and I think it proved to be so.

2230
01:42:39.170 --> 01:42:42.381
He wrote an anthem.
It's a simplistic anthem,


2231
01:42:42.423 --> 01:42:45.593
but it's an anthem that has a
good heart and a good message


2232
01:42:45.634 --> 01:42:48.012
and that people have
been singing ever since.


2233
01:42:48.054 --> 01:42:50.890
["Give Peace A Chance"]

2234
01:42:53.266 --> 01:42:56.562
♪ Ev'rybody's talking
'bout Bagism, Shagism


2235
