01:45:24.417 --> 01:45:26.587
Well, we know actually

2284
01:45:26.628 --> 01:45:29.422
because so many groups
from that same period


2285
01:45:29.464 --> 01:45:31.592
continued and
continued and continued


2286
01:45:31.633 --> 01:45:34.262
when it most definitely
wasn't fun anymore.


2287
01:45:34.303 --> 01:45:36.931
The Beatles ended it
because the reasons


2288
01:45:36.972 --> 01:45:39.183
that they had
gotten into doing it


2289
01:45:39.225 --> 01:45:41.434
ceased to have value for them.

2290
01:45:41.476 --> 01:45:43.812
So they said, let's
not do this anymore.


2291
01:45:43.854 --> 01:45:48.859
That's as powerful a statement
about their integrity


2292
01:45:48.901 --> 01:45:51.153
and their intentions
and their values


2293
01:45:51.195 --> 01:45:53.239
as anything that I can think of.

2294
01:45:53.281 --> 01:45:55.741
[Narrator] In
The Beatles' wake,


2295
01:45:55.783 --> 01:45:58.077
youth culture
became more divided,


2296
01:45:58.119 --> 01:46:00.871
rock music got heavier
and more self-indulgent


2297
01:46:00.913 --> 01:46:03.498
and pop turned its
attention to glamor.


2298
01:46:03.540 --> 01:46:05.293
As for the band
members themselves,


2299
01:46:05.334 --> 01:46:07.836
despite Lennon's
continued activism


2300
01:46:07.878 --> 01:46:09.422
and string of hit singles,

2301
01:46:09.462 --> 01:46:12.258
McCartney's mainstream
triumph through his band Wings


2302
01:46:12.300 --> 01:46:14.343
and Harrison's
successful emergence


2303
01:46:14.385 --> 01:46:16.137
as an artist in his own right,

2304
01:46:16.178 --> 01:46:19.014
their impact as individuals
could never match that


2305
01:46:19.056 --> 01:46:21.142
of their Beatles glory days.

2306
01:46:21.183 --> 01:46:23.269
Yet although their
vision of utopia


2307
01:46:23.311 --> 01:46:25.104
had failed to materialize,

2308
01:46:25.146 --> 01:46:27.231
the world was still
forever changed


2309
01:46:27.273 --> 01:46:28.941
by The Beatles' innovations

2310
01:46:28.983 --> 01:46:31.235
and the values that
they represented.


2311
01:46:31.277 --> 01:46:33.904
Even if no one has ever managed
to compete with that impact,


2312
01:46:33.946 --> 01:46:37.450
with every successive
generation of musicians


2313
01:46:37.490 --> 01:46:39.868
The Beatles remain the benchmark

2314
01:46:39.910 --> 01:46:42.330
for how popular
entertainers can interact


2315
01:46:42.371 --> 01:46:43.956
with the wider world.

2316
01:46:43.998 --> 01:46:46.875
Did cultural and
musical changes,


2317
01:46:46.917 --> 01:46:49.003
to which they were
without any doubt


2318
01:46:49.044 --> 01:46:51.630
the largest contributors,
have a permanent effect


2319
01:46:51.672 --> 01:46:54.425
on how rock and roll
conceived itself?


2320
01:46:54.467 --> 01:46:56.093
Yeah, permanent effect

2321
01:46:56.135 --> 01:46:58.346
on how rock and roll
perceived itself.


2322
01:46:58.387 --> 01:47:02.224
So that there's even now
